@Comment:	to Jacob , how are you doing. I like going to your house. I hop you liked going over my house. Love Chris
@Comment:	context notes say Mot and Chi are sitting at the kitchen table; Chi has to deal with a lot of distractions (birds are flying around the room and making a lot of noise , MOT walks in and out to take care of Bro) but still manages to persevere and write a good letter. Chi gets help from EXP when Mot leaves the room , including telling him to sign letter. Chi decides who to write to but asks for Mot's help on what to write. She makes suggestions about punctuation but insists that Chi decide on the text himself <write something that comes to mind when you think of Jacob>; Chi seems to write slowly and carefully , and his spelling is quite good
